# Design Document Reference

The [DESIGN_DOC.md](mdc:DESIGN_DOC.md) contains the complete system architecture and specifications for Anypod. This document should be referenced when:

1. Understanding the system architecture
2. Checking configuration formats
3. Verifying database schema
4. Reviewing API endpoints
5. Understanding deployment requirements

Key sections include:
- Purpose and non-goals
- High-level architecture with Mermaid diagrams
- Configuration examples with YAML
- Database schema and status lifecycle
- Processing flow
- HTTP endpoints
- Command-line flags
- Deployment specifications
- Dependencies and tooling

All development work should align with the specifications in this document.
